Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of five (5) years.  Three (3) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 11-19-14 by 6:00 p.m.  Court will authorize travel outside the county for employment to Sheboygan.  
2) Pay costs of action;
3) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) Provide DNA sample;
5) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety;
7) Repay $170.00 buy money.
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment.  
